caption: b'This #GivingTuesday we\xe2\x80\x99ve partnered with @FeedingAmerica to focus on giving back to our communities and support those in need. With your help, we can do even more. Donate at the link in our bio. #FirstRepublicGives'

b'Caring deeply for our communities, clients and colleagues is core to who we are and First Republic colleague Lena Robinson demonstrates this daily. b'Our clients are the pick of the patch. On behalf of your team at First Republic, we wish you a safe and fun #Halloween.'

b'At First Republic, giving back to our communities is a part of who we are. This commitment is driven by extraordinary colleagues like Michelle who dedicate time every year to volunteer with their favorite nonprofit organizations. Thank you, Michelle, for exemplifying First Republic\xe2\x80\x99s commitment to service. #teamfirstrepublic'

b'The Bay Area Heart Walk looked a little different this year. Even in these challenging circumstances, First Republic colleagues from coast to coast found a way to demonstrate their care and support for @american_heart. #TeamFirstRepublic #HeartWalkBayArea #2020HeartWalk'

b'At First Republic, our focus is to listen to clients like @MassChallenge and meet them with an unparalleled level of service. MassChallenge has helped entrepreneurs from more than 54 countries solve some of the world\xe2\x80\x99s biggest challenges. The team works collaboratively to ensure that entrepreneurs get access to the right resources \xe2\x80\x94 including mentorship, programming and office space \xe2\x80\x94 at the right time based on their stage of growth. Read more about MassChallenge and other accomplished clients featured in our 2019 Annual Report. Link in bio. #startup #entrepreneur'

b'First Republic is proud to support clients like Martin Muoto in achieving their goals. Through his investment fund, @solaimpact, Martin helps preserve and develop high-quality, affordable housing in South Central LA. From serving historically neglected neighborhoods to providing scholarships for disadvantaged teens, everything Martin does is about creating opportunity. Read more about Martin and other accomplished clients featured in our 2019 Annual Report. Link in bio.'

b'As we look back on National Nurses Week, we want to thank our nurses and frontline healthcare professionals for their dedication to keeping our communities safe. We hope you enjoyed the hot meals, courtesy of First Republic. #NationalNursesWeek #NationalNursesDay'
b"Here's to the inspiring patience, wisdom and strength of moms everywhere. Tag a mom you want to honor. #MothersDay"

b"It's an honor to sponsor @AmericanBalletTheatre: Together Tonight \xe2\x80\x94 a virtual celebration in support of the ABT Crisis Relief Fund \xe2\x80\x94 on ABT\xe2\x80\x99s YouTube channel on May 12 at 7:00 p.m EDT. For 80 years, this renowned ballet company has danced across the world. For the first time ever, ABT will be dancing in your home."

b"It's a privilege to be the founding sponsors of #ParentTrapped, a new podcast created by the editors at @commonsenseorg. In response to the coronavirus, Common Sense Media offers a new parenting resource to capture parents' candid stories and moments where reality meets (comic) relief. Check the link in our bio to listen to the first episode."

b'In honor of #GivingTuesdayNow, our employees have teamed up with nonprofits through our COVID-19 Matching Gift Program and virtual volunteerism to support the communities where we live and work. We are partnering with Meals on Wheels (@mowsf), CityMeals on Wheels (@citymeals) in New York City and Ethos in Boston to craft and deliver uplifting cards for homebound seniors. We hope these cards will bring our senior neighbors a sense of comfort and a big smile during this challenging time.'

b'As we continue to respond to the impact of COVID-19, meeting the needs of those we serve remains our first order of business. To learn more and to download the guide, visit our resources page found at the link in our bio.'

b"At First Republic, caring for our clients, colleagues and communities is our top priority. We've implemented a number of precautionary measures and dedicated resources to ensure uninterrupted service and continued support in light of the evolving situation with the coronavirus and current market volatility. Our offices are open for business, and our operations are fully supported. You can access your accounts, securely deposit checks and contact your First Republic team from anywhere using our app. We are here to help. Please don\xe2\x80\x99t hesitate to reach out to your banker or wealth management professional. For more information, please visit the link in our bio."
